<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

<metal:portlets fill-slot="portlets">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:portlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">
  <div>
    <img alt="" src="/@@/question" />
    <a tal:attributes="href context/fmt:url" tal:content="context/title" />
  </div>

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">
    <metal:extra_info fill-slot="extra_info">
      <p>If so, you can point
          <span tal:replace="structure context/owner/fmt:link" /> to the
          relevant knowledge base article for
          <span tal:replace="view/faq_target/displayname"
                /><tal:can-create-faq
                      condition="view/faq_target/required:launchpad.Moderate">
          or <a href="+createfaq">create a new FAQ</a> yourself if it doesn't
          exist already
          </tal:can-create-faq>.
      </p>
    </metal:extra_info>
  </div>

</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>This page is used to answer the question by making a link to a FAQ
    document. 
  </p>
  <p>Select the appropriate FAQ using the radio buttons. The list of suggested
    FAQs is determined by searching for FAQs similar to the question title.
    You can change the suggested list by modifying the search used and clicking
    on the <b>Search</b> button.
  </p>
  <p>To remove the FAQ link, select the <b>No existing FAQs are relevant</b>
    option.
  </p>
  <p>The message that will be used to answer the question is displayed in the
    <b>Answer Message</b> field. The selected FAQ title will be automatically
    appended to this message.
  </p>
  <p>If you are the project owner or one of its answer contacts, you can
    create a new FAQ document if none of the existing ones apply.
  </p>
</metal:help>

</body>
</html>
